1
00:00:10,120 --> 00:00:11,120
(Previously)
Watch out!

2
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:14,120
Oh, no!

3
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:15,000
What's wrong?
My…

4
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:16,720
My necklace's gone!

5
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,840
Did the one who hit you take it?

6
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:19,480
Wait!

7
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,320
You thief! Give it back!

8
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:23,800
I'm returning it to you, and that's it.

9
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:27,600
Why was it okay when he touched my hand?

10
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:30,279
Damn it!

11
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:31,640
Ouch! Who did this?!

12
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:34,720
You started it.

13
00:00:34,721 --> 00:00:35,879
You want a piece of me?

14
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:37,120
What if I do?

15
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,000
"Love Like a Bike" (Episode 2)

16
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:48,920
Mom,

17
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:51,000
since when did we hire this baker?

18
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,920
And when was the tasting?
How come I wasn't told?

19
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:58,120
You weren't here when
he came for the tasting yesterday.

20
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:00,400
His desserts are amazing.

21
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:03,400
He even has experience
in a Thai dessert shop.

22
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:04,800
P'Tawan,

23
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:08,200
his desserts are to die
for. You've got to try.

24
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:16,360
No thanks.

25
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,120
Your loss.

26
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,000
Suit yourself.

27
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:23,360
Dindin, let's get to work.

28
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,080
You got it.

29
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,280
Something going on… between you two?

30
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:36,040
Nothing!

31
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,400
Ooh, suspicious…

32
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:02,520
Don't think I've
forgotten about that night.

33
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,680
Not my fault. I tried to wake you,
but you wouldn't budge.

34
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:31,080
Are you a "hit and run" guy?

35
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:34,840
It was just a "friends
with benefits" thing.

36
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,680
Haven't you heard of it?

37
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,440
But you left me there alone,

38
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:41,320
completely naked.

39
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:45,000
You wouldn't wake up.

40
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:47,320
I even covered you with your clothes.

41
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:51,480
The wind must've blown
them away. I had to get to work.

42
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:54,800
Unlike you, I actually have a job to do.

43
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:59,640
- Are you pissing me off?
- I'm not. You're the one nagging me.

44
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:01,560
Do you want these croissants or not?

45
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:08,480
We've got a rush order!
Ten boxes of eclairs for a regular, ASAP!

46
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,560
Right now? I'm making croissants.

47
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,800
It'll have to wait. Baking takes time.

48
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,280
Please?!

49
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,200
Come on…

50
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:17,480
Please, please, please?

51
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:22,120
Fine. I'll get right on it.

52
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,480
Thanks!

53
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:32,840
Why are you still here,
old man? You're in my way.

54
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:36,200
Just do your job. I'm staying right here.

55
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,840
Nothing better to do?

56
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,120
I do now.

57
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:44,600
I don't trust you. Who knows
what you might steal from here.

58
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:46,320
You're nuts.

59
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:34,080
Hello. Do you have an appointment?

60
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:37,040
Ah, no… I don't.

61
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:40,360
I'm actually here to see Dr. Nabnueng.

62
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:45,680
Oh, he's out for field work today.

63
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,320
Field work?

64
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:51,320
Yes, our doctors take turns going out.

65
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:55,360
To support those at risk
of mental health issues.

66
00:05:55,760 --> 00:06:00,120
Including the homeless,
nightlife workers, and those…

67
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:03,120
with limited access to care.

68
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,360
Interesting.

69
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:12,480
May I ask, are you one of his patients?

70
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,640
N-no... not really.

71
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:19,880
Actually, yes. I just became one.

72
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:27,360
Do you happen to know where he is today?

73
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:30,960
Yes, I do.

74
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:38,640
Doctor, I'm so scared.

75
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:46,080
There's no legal protection for people
like us. Only criminal laws that punish us.

76
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:51,480
The recent events have left us terrified.

77
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:55,160
I don't know where to turn or what to do.

78
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:58,080
I hear you.

79
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:02,480
What you've been through...
must be traumatizing.

80
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:10,640
Yes. But it's worse when we're alone.
With no way out, we feel more depressed.

81
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,520
What makes you feel
that way at those times?

82
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:17,880
Maybe we're just exhausted from work.

83
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:21,680
Society, the economy, the unstable income.

84
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:24,280
No one will hire us for any other job.

85
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:27,000
I'm at the end of my rope, doctor.

86
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,480
I understand.

87
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,680
You have every right to feel exhausted.

88
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,000
Everyone here…

89
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:35,800
has the right to feel
whatever you're feeling.

90
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:39,320
But the most important thing is:

91
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:41,480
Please don't carry it all alone.

92
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:46,440
Reach out to those
around you—friends, or even me.

93
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:50,280
Talk about it. Share your burdens with us.

94
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,960
We'll find a way through this together.

95
00:07:55,800 --> 00:08:02,960
If anyone has something
too personal for a group setting,

96
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,920
you're welcome to speak with me privately.

97
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:06,840
Thank you.

98
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:32,520
Sailom?

99
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:36,520
What brings you here?

100
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:42,400
Oh… I was just passing by.

101
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:46,320
What about you? What are you doing here?

102
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:53,840
Field work with the SWING Foundation.
Providing counseling for those in nightlife.

103
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:56,880
They deserve the same
protections as everyone else.

104
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,200
I see.

105
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:05,000
I thought you only saw patients at the
clinic. I didn't expect to see you out here.

106
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:07,440
I just want to help out however I can.

107
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:13,800
Are you hungry?

108
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:15,680
Huh?

109
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:17,280
Hungry for what?

110
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:20,800
Hungry for dinner. Want to go grab a bite?

111
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,720
Still not done?

112
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:47,000
Not even close. They're bickering like crazy
in there. The filling's taking forever.

113
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:48,560
What are they fighting about?

114
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:51,840
P'Tawan's been hovering
in the kitchen all day.

115
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:56,560
They've been at it for an hour.
So many éclairs wasted.

116
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,400
Are we gonna make it in time?

117
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:04,760
No clue. See for yourself.

118
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:08,600
Nah, P'Tawan will just yell at me.

119
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,800
So... what now?

120
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:22,360
How much longer are you gonna stare?

121
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:27,040
Damn it…

122
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:32,400
Look! It's ruined because you keep staring.

123
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,600
It's all messy now.

124
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,600
How can I finish them on time?

125
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,160
Seriously,

126
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,440
have you ever even baked before?

127
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:47,120
I don't think you have.

128
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:51,160
If you're an expert,

129
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,200
do it yourself.

130
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:56,960
Me?

131
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:03,520
If I could, why would my mom hire you?

132
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,520
If you're still staring,

133
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:13,600
I'm not doing it.

134
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:07,760
How long have you been
away from Thailand for?

135
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:12,120
About… seven years or so, I think?

136
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:15,440
Why did you move to the US back then?

137
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:23,400
Come and play with me.

138
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:24,800
No, I don't want to!

139
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,680
- It's just your dad!
- Let go!

140
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,320
No! Leave me alone!

141
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,680
- I am your dad!
- Let me go!

142
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:31,960
I said, stay still!

143
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:33,160
Let me go!

144
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:35,600
Get over here! Now!

145
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:40,960
I'm sorry. If it's too personal,
you don't have to tell me.

146
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,560
Let's eat. You must be starving by now.

147
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:52,080
Order whatever you like.

148
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,080
It's my treat.

149
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,960
Menu, please?

150
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:06,680
Can you eat this?

151
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,000
Thank you.

152
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:20,880
Honestly,

153
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:25,000
it would be great if sex work
were fully decriminalized.

154
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:31,160
The workers wouldn't have to be
victims like in those tragic news items.

155
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:33,360
Yes, I agree.

156
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:37,200
It would be much safer for them.

157
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,280
They'd have welfare,

158
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:41,040
the state would get the tax,

159
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,800
and they'd be protected
from being exploited.

160
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,360
Most importantly:

161
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:48,920
They wouldn't be lured and killed.

162
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:53,160
It's devastating.

163
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,960
Let's toast.

164
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:01,520
No more heavy talk.

165
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,000
Cheers!

166
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,760
Whoa, easy!

167
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:20,200
Take it slow, or you'll get drunk.

168
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:25,400
I'm fine, Doc. I can handle this much.

169
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:06,280
"Not drunk at all," huh?

170
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:20,640
Look who finally decided to show up.
I thought a customer had locked you away.

171
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:22,240
No one can cage me, and you know it.

172
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:25,920
Can't be too sure. You're way too hot.

173
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:29,640
Everyone was dying to see you yesterday.

174
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:33,040
Especially that hottie at
that table over there.

175
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:46,960
You mean P'Man?

176
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:49,240
That influencer from Suphanburi.

177
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:53,920
Go charm him tonight.
He might drop a 500-drink bid on you.

178
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:56,000
In your dreams.

179
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:57,680
Just give it a shot.

180
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,159
Welcome to The Loner Club.
We're here to cure your loneliness.

181
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:06,680
Let the drink bidding begin!

182
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:10,840
Okay, here's Number 88 from Table V2.

183
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:15,520
10 drinks for Number 88 from Table V2!
Going once… going twice… SOLD!

184
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:18,880
Ice, Number 88, you're heading to V2!

185
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:21,440
Any more bids?

186
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:23,239
Number 69, 50 drinks!

187
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:25,079
Ooh! 50 drinks for 69!

188
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:29,159
Going once... twice...

189
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:29,680
going...

190
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:33,159
- 100 drinks!
- 100 drinks from Table 27!

191
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:35,199
Going once…

192
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:36,200
twice...

193
00:16:36,201 --> 00:16:38,599
- Make it 120!
- 120 drinks!

194
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:42,000
120 drinks. Going once… twice…

195
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:44,000
and finally...

196
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,960
200 drinks.

197
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:53,080
200 drinks! Alright!
Going once… twice…

198
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:57,719
Sold! Table 17 takes the whole set!

199
00:16:57,720 --> 00:17:01,920
Sky is officially off the floor
tonight! Congratulations!

200
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:04,120
Thank you so much, sir, for...

201
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:16,040
You're hot.

202
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:22,680
Number 28, 100 drinks!

203
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:24,879
Number 28, 100 drinks!

204
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:32,520
Number 28. Going once… twice…
SOLD! Off to P'Man's table!

205
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:35,680
He's off the floor as well!

206
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:38,760
What are you drinking?
Want me to fix you a glass?

207
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:41,960
Whiskey with soda, or just water?

208
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:44,279
Whiskey and water...

209
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:44,960
Alright.

210
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:47,599
Number 8? How many drinks for Number 8?

211
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:52,519
- Two drinks.
- Oh, two drinks from Table 27.

212
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:58,040
Going once... twice... SOLD! To Table 27!

213
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:04,360
Have some water first.

214
00:18:06,080 --> 00:18:07,800
You can really hold your liquor.

215
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:15,200
This is my first time.
Didn't know it'd... feel this good.

216
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:17,800
- Your first time drinking?
- Yup.

217
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:19,800
- First time at a host club too?
- Mm-hmm.

218
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:22,520
Do you like it?

219
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:25,280
I do.

220
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:34,640
So, what can you do besides mixing drinks?

221
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,040
I can…

222
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:39,320
play games, mix drinks…

223
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:42,200
Basically, I can do whatever you want.

224
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,000
Anything I want?

225
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:46,840
Then… show me what you've got.

226
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:55,880
Good boy. Here's your reward.

227
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:01,000
Easy there.

228
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:02,920
You should have some water.

229
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:07,920
Drink up. You'll feel better.

230
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:11,800
You okay?

231
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:15,520
The whiskey... it's gone. I need...

232
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:18,280
Hey. Another bottle over here.

233
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:23,120
- Let's stick with water for now.
- No. I want another bottle.

234
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:28,280
Please have some water first.

235
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:38,320
You bastards!

236
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:41,800
I'm just an old woman!
How can you be so heartless?!

237
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:43,720
Shut up, old hag!

238
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:46,080
It's your own fault for not paying us back.

239
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:49,200
If we did, we would've paid you by now!

240
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:52,680
And why is the interest so damn high?!

241
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:54,520
We pay so much,
but the debt never goes away!

242
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,240
You've got a big mouth!

243
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:58,200
Hey!

244
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:01,640
Get your hands off my grandma!

245
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:05,800
Are you okay?

246
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:09,080
Like mother, like son.

247
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:12,320
A deadbeat, just like your mom.

248
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:16,440
No, Dindin! Please don't!

249
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:19,400
I was gonna give you more time.

250
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,720
But on second thought,

251
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:24,240
taking your house is much easier.

252
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:26,920
You can't do that! We had a deal!

253
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:29,240
But you've got nothing for my boss.

254
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:32,560
I have it.

255
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:35,280
I'll transfer it right now.

256
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:46,160
3,000?! That doesn't
even cover the interest!

257
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:51,840
Just take it. That's all I have.

258
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:56,040
Let's go.

259
00:20:57,520 --> 00:20:59,680
Better than nothing, I guess.

260
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:07,400
Are you hurt, Grandma?

261
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:34,560
Hey, is that that pilot?

262
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,280
Which one?

263
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:41,040
The one who botched
that landing and killed a kid.

264
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:44,680
The guy from that viral TikTok?

265
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:50,440
Oh, right. That girl was
the same age as my sister.

266
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:54,920
Feel bad for her parents.
She was at such a sweet age.

267
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:57,360
But she's gone because
